                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18201028-128-off697 t18201028-128-crimeloc699"></join>, and saw a man take a coat off Lowe's cart and give it to the prisoner. I pointed out both the men to my father; he ran and brought the coat back but not the prisoner. I am sure he is the man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18201028-128-person1238">
                  THOMAS 
                  DEAKIN
               <interp inst="t18201028-128-person1238" type="surname" value="DEAKIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18201028-128-person1238" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18201028-128-person1238" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I heard the alarm, and pursued the prisoner down Sanders's-gardens, he was stopped and liberated again - I followed him. His companions struck me several times; I caught him in Hoxton-square - he said I was not an officer, and had no right to detain him, I said I should.</p>
               <p>
            
